  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "f4d549ae1f37453fb970c9c756012c7f",
        "content": [
          "=== DATA SOURCES ===\n",
          "1. system.query.history — raw query history with structs (compute, query_source) and byte/ms units.\n",
          "2. ryant_catalog.default.query_history_mv — METRIC VIEW with pre-defined measures and dimensions.\n",
          "\n",
          "=== WHEN TO USE EACH SOURCE ===\n",
          "METRIC VIEW: Use for aggregate/KPI questions — totals, averages, rates, percentiles, counts by dimension.\n",
          "  Syntax: SELECT dim, MEASURE(`measure_name`) FROM ryant_catalog.default.query_history_mv WHERE ... GROUP BY ALL\n",
          "  Filter on `Query Date` (date type) for the metric view, not `Start Time`.\n",
          "RAW TABLE: Use when user needs statement_text, error_message, query_tags, individual query details, or columns not in the metric view.\n",
          "  Filter on start_time (timestamp) for the raw table.\n",
          "\n",
          "=== TIME FILTERING (REQUIRED) ===\n",
          "Always apply a time filter. Default to last 7 days if not specified.\n",
          "  Metric view: `Query Date` >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  Raw table: start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "\n",
          "=== RAW TABLE TIPS ===\n",
          "Structs: compute.warehouse_id, compute.type, query_source.notebook_id, query_source.dashboard_id, query_source.job_info.job_id (nested!), query_source.pipeline_info.pipeline_id (nested!).\n",
          "Convert bytes to GB: divide by 1024*1024*1024. Convert ms to seconds: divide by 1000.\n",
          "Use try_divide() to avoid division by zero. \n",
          "execution_status: FINISHED, FAILED, CANCELED. Filter to FINISHED for perf analysis.\n",
          "Cost proxy: total_duration_ms — longer duration = more DBU consumption.\n",
          "For detail queries (individual slow/spill/failed queries), always include statement_id so users can look up the query in Query History.\n",
          "\n",
          "=== METRIC VIEW MEASURES ===\n",
          "Volume: Total Queries, Unique Users, Warehouses Used\n",
          "Duration: Avg/Max/P50/P95/P99 Duration Sec, Total Duration Sec\n",
          "Wait: Total Compute Wait Sec, Total Capacity Wait Sec, Avg Wait Pct\n",
          "Data: Total Read GB/TB, Total Written/Shuffle/Spill GB\n",
          "Flags: Slow/Very Slow/Spill/Failed/Cached/Long Wait/Poor Scan Query Count\n",
          "Rates: Cache Hit Rate Pct, Failure Rate Pct, Spill Rate Pct\n",
          "\n",
          "When asked about data read in TB, use MEASURE(`Total Read TB`). When asked about data read in GB, use MEASURE(`Total Read GB`). Do NOT use Total Queries for data volume questions.\n",
          "\n",
          "=== METRIC VIEW DIMENSIONS ===\n",
          "Time: Start Time, Query Date, Query Hour, Day of Week\n",
          "Identity: Executed By, Warehouse ID, Workspace ID\n",
          "Classification: Statement Type, Execution Status, Query Source Type, Client Application\n",
          "Flags: Is Slow Query, Has Disk Spill, Is Cached, Is Tableau, Is Power BI, Is dbt\n",
          "IDs: Notebook/Dashboard/Job/Alert/Genie Space/Pipeline/SQL Query ID\n",
          "\n",
          "=== QUERY SOURCE vs CLIENT APPLICATION ===\n",
          "Query Source Type = which Databricks entity triggered the query (Notebook, Dashboard, Job, etc.).\n",
          "Client Application = which external tool connected (Tableau, Power BI, dbt).\n",
          "These are different dimensions — use the right one based on the question."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "example_question_sqls": [
      {
        "id": "21927bcbfe8643069b759960d26fe0a7",
        "question": [
          "Duration breakdown — where is time spent for the slowest queries?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT executed_by,\n",
          "  statement_text,\n",
          "  waiting_for_compute_duration_ms / 1000 AS compute_wait_sec,\n",
          "  waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms / 1000 AS queue_wait_sec,\n",
          "  compilation_duration_ms / 1000 AS compile_sec,\n",
          "  execution_duration_ms / 1000 AS exec_sec,\n",
          "  result_fetch_duration_ms / 1000 AS fetch_sec,\n",
          "  total_duration_ms / 1000 AS total_sec\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND execution_status = 'FINISHED'\n",
          "ORDER BY total_duration_ms DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 10"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "29841b832d784c769d8eb761dd5fbc88",
        "question": [
          "Which Genie spaces generate the most queries?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT query_source.genie_space_id,\n",
          "  COUNT(*) AS query_count,\n",
          "  COUNT(DISTINCT executed_by) AS unique_users,\n",
          "  ROUND(try_divide(AVG(total_duration_ms), 1000), 2) AS avg_duration_sec\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND query_source.genie_space_id IS NOT NULL\n",
          "GROUP BY query_source.genie_space_id\n",
          "ORDER BY query_count DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 10"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "2c22998aaa5646b28704389a0c201f02",
        "question": [
          "Who is writing the most data?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT executed_by,\n",
          "  COUNT(*) AS write_queries,\n",
          "  SUM(written_bytes) / (1024*1024*1024) AS written_gb,\n",
          "  SUM(written_rows) AS total_rows_written\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND written_bytes > 0\n",
          "GROUP BY executed_by\n",
          "ORDER BY written_gb DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 10"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "35ca4fa697d64b2c87087d2531c3dc32",
        "question": [
          "Show me queries that are both slow and have disk spill"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT statement_id,\n",
          "  executed_by,\n",
          "  statement_text,\n",
          "  try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000) AS duration_sec,\n",
          "  try_divide(spilled_local_bytes, 1024*1024*1024) AS spilled_gb,\n",
          "  start_time\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND total_duration_ms > 60000\n",
          "  AND spilled_local_bytes > 0\n",
          "ORDER BY duration_sec DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 20"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "375af4e848b44335b5855175ecb3e5e0",
        "question": [
          "Which dashboards drive the most queries?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT\n",
          "  COALESCE(query_source.dashboard_id, query_source.legacy_dashboard_id) AS dashboard_id,\n",
          "  CASE WHEN query_source.dashboard_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI/BI' ELSE 'Legacy' END AS dashboard_type,\n",
          "  COUNT(*) AS query_count,\n",
          "  COUNT(DISTINCT executed_by) AS unique_viewers,\n",
          "  ROUND(try_divide(AVG(total_duration_ms), 1000), 2) AS avg_duration_sec\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND (query_source.dashboard_id IS NOT NULL OR query_source.legacy_dashboard_id IS NOT NULL)\n",
          "GROUP BY dashboard_id, dashboard_type\n",
          "ORDER BY query_count DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 10"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "4c3f335715bb4da89f9d1b19e8daac09",
        "question": [
          "What is the cache hit rate and spill rate by warehouse?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT `Warehouse ID`,\n",
          "  MEASURE(`Total Queries`) AS total_queries,\n",
          "  MEASURE(`Cache Hit Rate Pct`) AS cache_hit_rate_pct,\n",
          "  MEASURE(`Spill Rate Pct`) AS spill_rate_pct\n",
          "FROM ryant_catalog.default.query_history_mv\n",
          "WHERE `Query Date` >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND `Warehouse ID` IS NOT NULL\n",
          "GROUP BY ALL\n",
          "ORDER BY total_queries DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "57009ec60edd443c8312a3051d5ba332",
        "question": [
          "What is the P95 query duration by warehouse this week?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT `Warehouse ID`,\n",
          "  MEASURE(`P95 Duration Sec`) AS p95_duration_sec\n",
          "FROM ryant_catalog.default.query_history_mv\n",
          "WHERE `Query Date` >= DATE_TRUNC('WEEK', CURRENT_DATE)\n",
          "  AND `Warehouse ID` IS NOT NULL\n",
          "GROUP BY ALL\n",
          "ORDER BY p95_duration_sec DESC"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "57fb0b8789b74c9cb90a06f71ef0aa37",
        "question": [
          "Which queries read the most data?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT statement_id,\n",
          "  executed_by,\n",
          "  statement_text,\n",
          "  read_bytes / (1024*1024*1024) AS read_gb,\n",
          "  read_rows,\n",
          "  total_duration_ms / 1000 AS duration_sec\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND execution_status = 'FINISHED'\n",
          "ORDER BY read_bytes DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 10"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "5ccc308a32cb42c6949bf1d5cc40ca38",
        "question": [
          "Which queries are waiting the longest for compute?"
        ],
        "sql": [
          "SELECT executed_by,\n",
          "  compute.warehouse_id,\n",
          "  statement_text,\n",
          "  waiting_for_compute_duration_ms / 1000 AS compute_wait_sec,\n",
          "  waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms / 1000 AS capacity_wait_sec,\n",
          "  total_duration_ms / 1000 AS total_sec\n",
          "FROM system.query.history\n",
          "WHERE start_time >= current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS\n",
          "  AND (waiting_for_compute_duration_ms > 30000 OR waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms > 30000)\n",
          "ORDER BY waiting_for_compute_duration_ms + waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms DESC\n",
          "LIMIT 20"
        ]
      },
      {
